<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span>New York Office</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Wachsman PR is seeking an accomplished Senior Account Executive for its New York office. The Senior Account Executive will be responsible for all aspects of day-to-day account execution, reporting to an Account Supervisor. The successful candidate will plan and execute PR campaigns and develop relationships with reporters based in the U.S. and abroad. Occasional travel may be required.</p>
<p>Duties:</p>
<ul>
<li>Planning and executing PR campaigns</li>
<li>Managing day-to-day internal and external communications on behalf of clients</li>
<li>Drafting, editing and distributing press materials</li>
<li>Dealing with enquiries from press, clients, new business and external organizations</li>
<li>Conducting one-on-one client engagement</li>
<li>Undertaking industry research and generating story ideas/angles</li>
<li>Developing and maintaining relationships with U.S. and international media to secure coverage</li>
<li>Managing, supporting, and training junior team members</li>
</ul>
<p>The successful applicant will have:</p>
<ul>
<li>At least 3 years&rsquo; PR agency experience</li>
<li>Exceptional work ethic and motivated to excel in a fast-paced environment</li>
<li>Outstanding interpersonal and written and verbal communication skills</li>
<li>Track record of securing media coverage and experience in developing relationships with reporters</li>
<li>Ability to think strategically about developing PR campaigns</li>
<li>Excellent organizational skills and exceptional attention to detail</li>
<li>Ability to work well in a team</li>
<li>Experience leading junior staff effectively</li>
<li>Ideally a background in technology and/or financial services PR</li>
</ul>
<p>Candidates should send a CV and cover letter with salary expectations to <a href="mailto:newyork@wachsmanpr.com">newyork@wachsmanpr.com</a></p>